The paper focuses on data streaming and continuous queries, which are commonly studied in the database community (cs.DB). It also discusses the use of data structures to maintain the state of streaming operators, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of shared objects and lock-free algorithms, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
